[b]Relative Leg Efficiency — Panel + Chart[/b] is the companion panel indicator to the RLE overlay, adding a dedicated pane that plots both live (in-progress) and confirmed (closed) efficiency scores over time.

[b]What it does[/b]

While the overlay version draws leg lines and labels on the price chart, this script extends the visualization into a separate panel: confirmed RLE scores are plotted as a historical series, and the live score updates bar by bar as the current leg develops. Together they give both a spatial view (where on the chart the leg happened) and a temporal view (how RLE has been trending over recent bars).

[b]Features[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Panel pane[/b] — Dedicated panel plotting live and confirmed RLE scores as separate series
[*][b]Chart overlay[/b] — Leg lines and pivot labels with ATR-based label offsets, same as the standalone version
[*][b]Counter-pressure modes[/b] — Body-weighted or candle-count based pressure measurement
[*][b]Live + confirmed[/b] — In-progress score visible alongside historical confirmed values
[/list]

Best used alongside [b]relative_leg_efficiency.pine[/b] if you want the overlay alone, or as a replacement that includes both views in one script.

